\\"ladi-shape\\\">&nbsp;<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-element\\\" id=\\\"SHAPE7088\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-shape\\\">&nbsp;<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-element\\\" id=\\\"SHAPE7089\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-shape\\\">&nbsp;<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-element\\\" id=\\\"GROUP6989\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-group\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-element\\\" id=\\\"IMAGE6911\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-image\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-image-background\\\">&nbsp;<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-element\\\" id=\\\"PARAGRAPH7056\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-paragraph\\\">3<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-element\\\" id=\\\"PARAGRAPH7057\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-paragraph\\\">Daily Routine<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-element\\\" id=\\\"PARAGRAPH7058\\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\\"ladi-paragraph\\\">The daily routine for your child follows the rule of &quot;Eat-Play-Sleep.&quot; It means that when your baby wakes up, they will be fed when hungry, followed by playtime, and then put to sleep when they show signs of tiredness. This routine is repeated throughout the day until bedtime.<br \\/>\\r\\nThe timing of feeding, wakefulness, and sleep for each baby at different stages varies and depends entirely on their individual needs. By observing signals such as hunger and sleepiness, parents can accurately meet their child&#39;s needs.<br \\/>\\r\\nA baby who follows a suitable daily routine will feel full, get enough sleep, and have longer nighttime sleep. When their needs are met accurately, they will be happy and smiling.<br \\/>\\r\\nAlong with a suitable daily routine, when a baby reaches a weight of 6-7kg, they are ready to store enough energy during the day and can sleep through the night for 10-12 hours without feeding.<br \\/>\\r\\nThis is also the time when parents can enjoy